Patch Set 5:

Hi John, I have loaded your code and debug in local, the blocking happened on https://review.openstack.org/#/c/45335/5/glance/db/sqlalchemy/migrate_repo/versions/029_location_meta_data_pickle_to_string.py L47, that is old 'meta_data' column removing. And it seems the root cause is you miss disconnect form the connection which you using migrate meta_data record. I can resolve the blocking by adding 'conn.close()' to line L47. An example: https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/db/sqlalchemy/migrate_repo/versions/003_add_disk_format.py#L152 . Any thoughts?

Patch Set 5:

Good catching, zhiyan. I just verified it by downloading the code and ran it in my development environment. @jbresnah, I think you need add conn.close() in line 47 and line 73 to fix current blocker. Good luck :)
